RABIES, HUMAN - UK: BACKGROUND
******************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
See Also
Rabies, human - UK ex Philippines 20010510.0907
Date: 12 May 2001
From: Stephen A. Berger, M.D. <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
Source: GIDEON <http://www.cyinfo.com>

The last indigenous human case was reported in 1902. Seventeen imported
cases were registered during 1946 to 1985 (most from India, Pakistan,
Zambia and Bangladesh). One case was reported in 1986; 1 in 1987; 1 in
1988; 0 during 1989 to 1995.
A single case was reported in 1996 (imported from Nigeria - acquired from
a dog bite). No cases were reported during 1997 to 1999.
Post-exposure treatment courses were administered 768 times in 1988; 596 in
1989; 31 in 1990; 439 in 1992; 566 in 1993; 495 in 1994; 438 in 1995; 480
in 1996; 472 in 1997; 491 in 1998.
No rabid bats were identified during 1970 to 1995. A rabid insectivorous
bat was identified in Newhaven in 1996 (4 human contacts were given
prophylaxis). No rabid bats were reported during 1997 to 1998. The last
rabid dog died in quarantine in 1972. None of 200 000 dogs and
cats imported during 1972 to 1996 was found rabid during quarantine.
--
Stephen A. Berger, M.D.
<mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
